How can I compute the Hamming Distance between two strings, given the following JSON data format for String 1 and String 2?
{
  "string1": {
    "chars": ["c", "a", "t"]
  },
  "string2": {
    "chars": ["a", "c", "t"]
  }
}
And how can I use the following JSON data code to achieve this computation?
{
  "code": {
    "python": "def hamming_distance(s1, s2):\n    if len(s1) != len(s2):\n        raise ValueError('Strings must be of equal length')\n    return sum(ch1 != ch2 for ch1, ch2 in zip(s1, s2))"
  }
}
